# Quote of the Day — Flutter

This single-file Flutter project contains a complete demo app implementing your requirements: daily quote, share, favorites, refresh on launch, attractive UI, and instructions to record & upload a demo.

---

## pubspec.yaml (dependencies)

```yaml
name: quote_of_the_day
description: A simple Quote of the Day app demo
publish_to: 'none'
version: 1.0.0+1

environment:
  sdk: '>=2.18.0 <3.0.0'

dependencies:
  flutter:
    sdk: flutter
  shared_preferences: ^2.0.15
  share_plus: ^6.3.0

dev_dependencies:
  flutter_test:
    sdk: flutter

flutter:
  uses-material-design: true
```

---

## lib/main.dart

```dart
import 'dart:convert';
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:shared_preferences/shared_preferences.dart';
import 'package:share_plus/share_plus.dart';

void main() async {
  WidgetsFlutterBinding.ensureInitialized();
  runApp(QuoteOfTheDayApp());
}

class Quote {
  final String text;
  final String author;
  Quote({required this.text, this.author = ''});

  Map<String, String> toJson() => {'text': text, 'author': author};
  factory Quote.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> j) => Quote(text: j['text'], author: j['author'] ?? '');
}

class QuoteOfTheDayApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      title: 'Quote of the Day',
      theme: ThemeData(
        primarySwatch: Colors.indigo,
        visualDensity: VisualDensity.adaptivePlatformDensity,
      ),
      home: HomeScreen(),
      debugShowCheckedModeBanner: false,
    );
  }
}

class HomeScreen extends StatefulWidget {
  @override
  _HomeScreenState createState() => _HomeScreenState();
}

class _HomeScreenState extends State<HomeScreen> {
  late List<Quote> _quotes;
  late Quote _currentQuote;
  Set<String> _favorites = {}; // store JSON strings
  bool _loading = true;

  static const String favKey = 'favorite_quotes_v1';

  @override
  void initState() {
    super.initState();
    _quotes = _buildQuotes();
    _loadState();
  }

  List<Quote> _buildQuotes() {
    return [
      Quote(text: 'The only limit to our realization of tomorrow is our doubts of today.', author: 'Franklin D. Roosevelt'),
      Quote(text: 'Do not wait to strike till the iron is hot; but make it hot by striking.', author: 'William Butler Yeats'),
      Quote(text: 'Success is not final, failure is not fatal: it is the courage to continue that counts.', author: 'Winston Churchill'),
      Quote(text: 'What you get by achieving your goals is not as important as what you become by achieving your goals.', author: 'Zig Ziglar'),
      Quote(text: 'Believe you can and you’re halfway there.', author: 'Theodore Roosevelt'),
      Quote(text: 'Act as if what you do makes a difference. It does.', author: 'William James'),
      Quote(text: 'Success usually comes to those who are too busy to be looking for it.', author: 'Henry David Thoreau'),
      Quote(text: 'Keep your face always toward the sunshine—and shadows will fall behind you.', author: 'Walt Whitman'),
      Quote(text: 'The best way to predict the future is to invent it.', author: 'Alan Kay'),
      Quote(text: 'You miss 100% of the shots you don’t take.', author: 'Wayne Gretzky'),
      // add more quotes as desired
    ];
  }

  Future<void> _loadState() async {
    final prefs = await SharedPreferences.getInstance();
    final favList = prefs.getStringList(favKey) ?? [];
    _favorites = favList.toSet();

    _currentQuote = _quoteOfTheDay();

    setState(() => _loading = false);
  }

  Quote _quoteOfTheDay() {
    // Select quote deterministically based on current date so it changes once per day.
    final now = DateTime.now();
    final dateSeed = DateTime(now.year, now.month, now.day).millisecondsSinceEpoch;
    final index = (dateSeed ~/ 1000) % _quotes.length; // simple stable index
    return _quotes[index];
  }

  void _toggleFavorite(Quote q) async {
    final key = jsonEncode(q.toJson());
    final prefs = await SharedPreferences.getInstance();
    setState(() {
      if (_favorites.contains(key)) _favorites.remove(key);
      else _favorites.add(key);
    });
    await prefs.setStringList(favKey, _favorites.toList());
  }

  void _shareQuote(Quote q) {
    final text = '"${q.text}"${q.author.isNotEmpty ? '\n— ${q.author}' : ''}';
    Share.share(text);
  }

  void _showFavorites() {
    Navigator.of(context).push(MaterialPageRoute(builder: (_) => FavoritesScreen(favs: _favorites, onToggle: (key) async {
      final prefs = await SharedPreferences.getInstance();
      setState(() {
        if (_favorites.contains(key)) _favorites.remove(key);
        else _favorites.add(key);
      });
      await prefs.setStringList(favKey, _favorites.toList());
    })));
  }

  void _nextRandomQuote() {
    setState(() {
      _currentQuote = (_quotes..shuffle()).first;
    });
  }

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    if (_loading) return Scaffold(body: Center(child: CircularProgressIndicator()));

    final isFav = _favorites.contains(jsonEncode(_currentQuote.toJson()));

    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text('Quote of the Day'),
        actions: [
          IconButton(icon: Icon(Icons.star_border), onPressed: _showFavorites),
        ],
      ),
      body: Container(
        width: double.infinity,
        height: double.infinity,
        decoration: BoxDecoration(
          gradient: LinearGradient(
            begin: Alignment.topLeft,
            end: Alignment.bottomRight,
            colors: [Colors.indigo.shade600, Colors.blue.shade300],
          ),
        ),
        padding: EdgeInsets.all(24),
        child: Column(
          mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.center,
          children: [
            Card(
              elevation: 8,
              shape: RoundedRectangleBorder(borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(16)),
              child: Padding(
                padding: const EdgeInsets.all(20.0),
                child: Column(
                  mainAxisSize: MainAxisSize.min,
                  children: [
                    Text('QUOTE OF THE DAY', style: TextStyle(fontSize: 12, letterSpacing: 1.6, color: Colors.grey[600])),
                    SizedBox(height: 8),
                    Text('"${_currentQuote.text}"',
                        style: TextStyle(fontSize: 22, height: 1.3, fontWeight: FontWeight.w600), textAlign: TextAlign.center),
                    SizedBox(height: 12),
                    if (_currentQuote.author.isNotEmpty)
                      Align(alignment: Alignment.centerRight, child: Text('— ${_currentQuote.author}', style: TextStyle(fontSize: 14, fontStyle: FontStyle.italic))),
                    SizedBox(height: 8),
                    Divider(),
                    Row(
                      mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.spaceBetween,
                      children: [
                        IconButton(
                          icon: Icon(isFav ? Icons.favorite : Icons.favorite_border, color: isFav ? Colors.red : null),
                          onPressed: () => _toggleFavorite(_currentQuote),
                          tooltip: 'Add to favorites',
                        ),
                        Row(children: [
                          ElevatedButton.icon(onPressed: () => _shareQuote(_currentQuote), icon: Icon(Icons.share), label: Text('Share')),
                          SizedBox(width: 8),
                          OutlinedButton(onPressed: _nextRandomQuote, child: Text('Next Quote')),
                        ])
                      ],
                    )
                  ],
                ),
              ),
            ),
            SizedBox(height: 24),
            Text('Last updated: ${DateTime.now().toLocal().toString().split('.').first}', style: TextStyle(color: Colors.white70)),
            SizedBox(height: 12),
            Text('Tip: The "Quote of the Day" updates once per day automatically (based on device date).', style: TextStyle(color: Colors.white70), textAlign: TextAlign.center),
          ],
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}

class FavoritesScreen extends StatelessWidget {
  final Set<String> favs;
  final Function(String) onToggle;
  FavoritesScreen({required this.favs, required this.onToggle});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    final list = favs.map((s) => Quote.fromJson(jsonDecode(s))).toList();

    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(title: Text('Favorites')),
      body: list.isEmpty
          ? Center(child: Text('No favorites yet. Add some from the Home screen!'))
          : ListView.separated(
              padding: EdgeInsets.all(12),
              itemBuilder: (_, i) {
                final q = list[i];
                final key = jsonEncode(q.toJson());
                return ListTile(
                  title: Text(q.text),
                  subtitle: q.author.isNotEmpty ? Text(q.author) : null,
                  trailing: IconButton(icon: Icon(Icons.delete), onPressed: () => onToggle(key)),
                );
              },
              separatorBuilder: (_, __) => Divider(),
              itemCount: list.length,
            ),
    );
  }
}
```

---

## How the "Quote of the Day" works
- The app deterministically chooses a quote from the built-in list using the device's date. That means the quote changes once per calendar day (according to the device timezone), and the same quote appears for anyone on that date if they use the same code + quote list.
- The "Next Quote" button lets the user see a random quote immediately.

---

## Running the app
1. Install Flutter (stable channel) and set up Android/iOS emulator or a device.
2. Create a new project or replace `lib/main.dart` and `pubspec.yaml` with the content above.
3. Run `flutter pub get`.
4. Run on device: `flutter run`.

---

## Recording a demo for YouTube (suggested script)
1. Open the app and show the "Quote of the Day" home screen.
2. Tap "Share" and demonstrate sharing dialog.
3. Add the quote to favorites, then open Favorites screen and remove it.
4. Show the "Next Quote" button behavior.
5. Close and re-open the app to show daily refresh (or change the device date to demonstrate a new day).
6. Mention the tech stack (Flutter, shared_preferences, share_plus).
7. Edit video title and description and upload to YouTube.

When uploaded, copy the YouTube video URL and submit it as required.

---

